==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stabat Mater
<hw>Sta"bat Ma"ter</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧"b⟦acr⟧t
m⟦amac⟧"t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>. <ety>[L., the mother was standing.]</ety> <def>A
celebrated Latin hymn, beginning with these words, commemorating the
sorrows of the mother of our Lord at the foot of the cross. It is read
in the Mass of the Sorrows of the Virgin Mary, and is sung by Catholics
when making ⟦ldquo⟧the way of the cross⟦rdquo⟧ (<xex>Via Crucis</xex>).
See <er>Station</er>, 7 <sd>(c)</sd>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

